Dating: PSAMMETICHUS I/WAHIBRE (not before); PSAMMETICHUS I/WAHIBRE; 26TH DYNASTY (not after)
Name: Impression of a seal
Description: This small impression of a seal in terracotta represents a king striking with a club a quadruped which he raises up by one hand. According to the cartouche which accompanies the scene, it was probably Psammetichus I. The object comes from the former collection of G. Hagemans
